      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Please do not stop taking your antibiotics just because your skin looks better; you must finish the entire course as prescribed. Stopping early is a common mistake that allows the toughest bacteria to survive, which is how infections become resistant to medicine. To ensure your skin is completely clear and the infection is eradicated, stick to the full dosage schedule. If you have any doubts, it's always best to follow the instructions given by your prescribing physician.",
