      "content": "Skipping the last week is a gamble, and the worst-case scenario is that you've only killed the weak bacteria, leaving the tough ones to multiply and become resistant. You might not notice it immediately, but the infection could flare up later, requiring stronger, more complicated treatments down the line. Since you feel fine, you are likely in the danger zone where the lingering bacteria are still active. For your own health, you must complete the full course to ensure total eradication.",
